description: JM AB engages in the business of real estate and property development activities. The company is headquartered in Solna, Stockholm and currently employs 2,472 full-time employees.  The firm is engaged in the acquisition of development properties, planning, pre-construction, production and sales of residential units, with its main focus being the expansion of metropolitan areas and university towns in Sweden, Denmark, Finland and Belgium. The company is also involved in project development of commercial premises and contract work, mainly in the Greater Stockholm area in Sweden. Its operations are structured into five business segments: JM Residential Stockholm, JM Residential Sweden, JM International, JM Property Development and JM Production. In Sweden the Company operates primarily under the JM brand, as well as under the Seniorgarden and Boratt names.
